author: @AninhaInvest
text: Música feita para o publico infanto juvenil, ensina a contar números. Ensina a falar as primeiras letras do alfabeto ABC, tem linguagem no vocativo e imperativo, o qual manda contar de 1 a 10. Novamente, Vocativo e imperativo  para contar de 1 a 3 que refere a escala de começar um trabalho ou exercício e também terminar alguma tarefa. Pedem para falar a palavra amor no vocativo. Perguntam sobre o que precisa o ouvinte da música e o que ele ou ela gostariam. Em termos educacionais, a música literalmente é instrutiva com valores considerados universais.

author: @armyonce5179
text:
ونس بما انو السينغل الانجليزي قرب فذي هي الطريقة الصحيحة لستريم سبوتيفاي اتبعوها ونشروها
-لحتى تسترمو طبعا اول شي لازم تفتحو حساب بسبوتيفاي وتسوو قائمة الستريم
-قائمة الستريم لازم يكون فيها اقل شي 10اغاني وتقدرو تطولوها لاكثر من3ساعات
-تقدرو تكررو الاغنية اكثر من3مرات بس لازم يكون بينها اغاني مختلفة مثلا لنقول كررنا مونرايز الي هو السينغل الجاي كثير مرات لازم نفصل بينه باغنية او ثنين ونتبهو مو اكثر من ثنين في الي يفصلوهم ب3يستحسن بثنين
-لازم الصوت يكون فوق النص
-ماتسوو اعادة للاغنية مباشرة
-بيين فترة وفترة وقفو الاغنية بالنص او تخطو اغنية عشان مايحسبكم روبوت
-لاتسترمو نفس القائمة سوو اكثر من وحدة سوولكم شي5او6قوائم وغيرو بينهم
-بالقائمة لازم يكون في3او4فنانين مختلفين فحطو فيها اغاني توايس ونايون وضيفو معهم اوست جيهيو او جونغيون او اغنية سانا الفردية
وبس وكذا تكونو سترمتو بشكل صحيح هالسينغل جدا مهم لو ضمنا نجاحه بنكون خلينا توايس يوصلو لمستوى جديد نجاحه يعتبر نقلة كبيرة بمسيرة توايس وحيضمن نجاح الميني البوم غير كذا في مخطط جديد بالشرق الاوسط وشمال افريقيا يعني مخصوص للعرب فلو سترمنا كويس بندخلهم مخطط ونثبت شعبية توايس بالبلدان العربية ومين يدري يمكن يضيفو بلد عربي للتور فلاتفصرو واذا انتو مشغولين عادي سوو قوائم طويلة حطو سماعات خلوها تشتغل وانتو نامو او سوو شي ثاني وبس توايس كثير تعبو وهم يحصرو للسينغل ولفعاليات عشاننا هالسنة الشركة غالبا بل اكيد ماحتدعم ولاتروج للسينغل فاقل شي خلونا ندعمهم
chou tzuyu

author: @julremnacua3282
text: I like the way their stylists brings out their individual identity. Personally, to suggest, Jeongyeon's body will be more complimented if stylists will put her on something that has flounces, pleats, and gathered seams but with caution. Those additional detail is better properly put on areas needing attention so the look won't be puffy. Something white, off-white, and very light plain pale pastel colors will do for her. Tryna imagine Jeongyeon under sexy curvy figurine. If there's sleeves on the design, it'll look better if it's plain stick to the skin sleeve than puffy, something see-through fabric will do as sleeve. This is only my own opinion because it seems that stylists want to put her on motion-constrained garments considering her new BMI. Stretchy fabrics will help her. I hope this helps. Disclaimer, I'm not a licensed professional stylist just a fashion enthusiast. Thank you 🌻

author: @morgandancer123
text:
I love this song to death but I don't like the fashion styling for this one. 
It seems like they intentionally put everyone in crop tops except for Jeongyeong. She's come such a long way the last 2 years and they should be giving her a more popping outfit.
Normally they have a better variety of looks that are still cohesive but unique (Fancy was amazing!) But for this one it just seemed odd. 

Love the song, love the choreo, get a new stylist.

text:

-اكيد اول واهم امفي هو Talk that Talk لانو توه نازل ولازم نرفع مشاهداته بسرعة عشان تزيد انجازاته ويقعد لاطول فترة بالمخططات العالمية

-فيديوهات أداء توايس بالmtv بقناة توايس الرسمية وبقنوات الmtv+فيديو كواليس تصوير مقاطع التيكتوك

text:
ونس اليوم يوم كثير مهم ذا اول حدث فاشن احضره داهيوم وهي اول عضوة تروح للفاشن ويك بنيويورك راح نحضر لحدث البراند العالمية مايكل كورس الماركة جدا معروفة يشتغلو مع أسماء كبيرة وسفيرتهم العالمية هي بيلا حديد فلازم نستغل هاليوم لدعم داهيون والترويج لها والترويج لعودة توايس فعشان تدعموها سوو الشغلات ذي
أولا لازم تجهزو حساباتكم بتويتر والفيس واليوتيوب برضووخاصة التويتر والانستا
_بالتويتر غردوا باسم داهيون وارفقو معه اسم Michel kors عشان تطلع بالسيرش تبع البراند ويتعرفو اللوكالز عليها
_رح نسوي ترندينق بارتي عشان نرفع داهيون بالترند هدفنا نخليها الاولى بالترند وباقي هاشتاقاتها تبقى بالصدارة ذي هي العبارات والهاشتاقات الي حنرفعها
Fashion Icon Dahyun
#DAHYUNxMichaelKors 
#DAHYUNonNYFW
#DAHYUN @JYPETWICE
_تفاعلوا بكل بوستات داهيون تبع البراند خاصة خاصة الي من الحسابات الرسمية سوولها لايك سيف انشروها بالستوري تفاعلو بالتعليقات وارفقو مع تعليقاتكم المنشن تبع حساب توايس وداهيون وهاشتاق اسم داهيون وتوايس بالكوري والعربي والانجليزي
_اكيد في حسابات رسمية وموثقة بالتويتر حتنزل عن داهيون وهي بالحدث فتفاعلو بكل هالحسابات سوو لايك ويتويت وعلقو عندهم بنفس العبارات والهاشتاقات هاذي
Fashion Icon Dahyun
#DAHYUNxMichaelKors 
#DAHYUNonNYFW
#DAHYUN @JYPETWICE

author: @isisgiza
text:
All of you talking about Jeongyeon's outfit not being like everyone else's. It reminds me of the angry people because Shuhua was the only one in Tomboy's outfits that didn't show her belly, and it's already been proven that she doesn't want to show too much. So like, as could be the stylists complicating it, it could just be her dealing with her body. I know what it's like to have low self-esteem and not want to wear your clothes like you used to because you can feel so ugly.
So you could stop judging her clothes and support her without mentioning that (I know many support her but still talk about her clothes), just remind her that she is amazing and special just like the other girls.

author: @isisgiza
text:
Todos vocês falando sobre a roupa da Jeongyeon não ser como as das outras. Isso me lembra da galera brava porque a Shuhua era a única que nos outfits de Tomboy não mostrava a barriga, e já foi comprovado que é ela que não quer mostrar demais. Então tipo, assim como podem ser os estilistas complicando, pode ser apenas ela lidando com o corpo dela. Eu sei o que é ter a autoestima baixa e não querer usar as roupas como antes porque você pode se achar muito feia.
Então vocês podiam parar de julgar as roupas dela e darem apoio sem mencionar isso (sei que muitos apoiam ela mas ainda falam das roupas), apenas relembrarem ela de que ela é incrível e especial assim como as outras meninas.

author: @joshuawong5839
text:
This is wonderful as usual. I wish that JYPE would also include the lyrics of the songs in their dance performance videos. The reason is that, of all the Kpop companies, the choreographies for JYPE groups emphasize the most on expressing the lyrics through dance. So it's really nice to see the connections between the lyrics and the dance moves for JYPE group songs - something that sets them apart from other companies like HYBE, SM and YG. It would also help foreign fans appreciate the lyrics of the songs more, I feel, once they can see the connections between the choreo and the lyrics.
+
Like in this song, for instance, when TWICE spells out "A to Z" (1:52) and L-O-V-E (2:00) with their hands, it goes by so fast it's not as obvious until you also know the lyrics to the song.

author: @gnvtwhp1218
text:
TW🤟❤️
To me, JYP/Twice made a song for the movie Dirty Dancing (1987). 
I imagine the movie Dirty Dancing (1987) in my head when I hear Talk That Talk. It's awesome. This song becomes 10x better when I imagine Patrick Swayze dancing with Jennifer Grey, falling in love. Jeninifer Grey being vulnerable. Patrick Swayze letting his facade down. Both of them opening up their hearts to let each other in through dancing. And then Patrick Swayze finally lifts her up (not saying I Love You but lifting her up and expressing BABY YOU MADE ME BETTER, Baby you're my world now, Baby we did this together). Yes. Dirty Dancing movie. An 80's reference probably 95% of the "Once" don't know about. I'm that old. I just have a nostalgia for the creative era of the 80's.

text: Finally....the video editors are back on track!!!  This is a great song with great choreography and amazing talent.  Each member was represented and could be clearly seen. These ladies work hard to perfect their performances and they deserve those behind the camera to give them excellent standards as well.  This is an upbeat fast paced song and you actually see them running to their spots which makes you feel the urge to get up and dance with them.  It felt like watching a live concert which is when they excel to their highest. (Just watch the live recording of "Touchdown" from "Twicelights in Seoul" to see the type of editing needed)  Also guess what...Nayeon, Sana, Tzuyu, and Dayhun can dance also.  Here lately all we see is a closeup of their vocals and then the camera jumps away. It's great to see them dancing their hearts out in the crowd when they're not singing. I am such a fan of these ladies and this video shows why!!! Excellent!!!
